g.text: A visual example of a route trie. Nodes represent path segments (static or parameter). Include a root node and child nodes for routes like '/api/users/:id' and '/api/posts'. Highlight the parameter node and the handler stored at leaf nodes.

ul.li: Each node represents a path segment.
Static segments (e.g., api, users) are exact matches.
Handlers are attached to leaf nodes that complete a route.
